Running tests for zmirror

Install dependencies (once):

::
  poetry install

Run the test suite:

::
  poetry run pytest tests -q

Run a specific test module:

::
  poetry run pytest tests/commands/test_commands.py -q
  poetry run pytest tests/requests/test_requests.py -q
  poetry run pytest tests/maintenance/test_maintenance.py -q

Run a single test:

::
  poetry run pytest tests/commands/test_commands.py::Tests::test_zdev_sysfs_s_offline -q

Run tests with a hard timeout (useful in CI or when debugging hangs):

::
  timeout 10s poetry run pytest tests -q

Notes:
- Prefer `poetry run pytest tests ...` instead of `poetry run pytest` so pytest does not try to collect from non-test folders.
- Most tests are stateful by module/class design; running single tests can behave differently from full ordered runs.
